@ Pertex I'm sorry to bother you but last year you wrote me a small program for allowing me to have a certain number of empty spaces from the left edge of the screen before I could start my text and that worked beautiful. Alas in 5.4 it totally ignores the program. I was wondering if you could tell me the difference, pretty please. lol.
 [color=#FF0040:3e25r7c2]&lt;function name=&quot;whitespaces&quot; parameters=&quot;number&quot; type=&quot;string&quot;&gt;&lt;![CDATA[
    text = &quot;&quot;
    for (x, 1, number) {
      text = text+ &quot; &quot;
    }
    return (&quot;&lt;b&gt;&quot;+text+&quot;&lt;/b&gt;&quot;)
  ]]&gt;&lt;/function&gt;[/color:3e25r7c2]
All I would have to write is whitespaces[color=#FF0040:3e25r7c2](number) + &quot;text&quot;[/color:3e25r7c2]
Thanks Terry.  <!-- s:D --><img src="{SMILIES_PATH}/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /><!-- s:D --> Happy Adventuring <!-- s:D --><img src="{SMILIES_PATH}/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /><!-- s:D -->

The output changed to html in Q5.4 so you can use this function now:

[code:2rt1rf6b]
 &lt;function name=&quot;whitespaces&quot; parameters=&quot;number&quot; type=&quot;string&quot;&gt;&lt;!&#91;CDATA&#91;
    text = &quot;&quot;
    for (x, 1, number, 1) {
      text = text+&quot;&amp;nbsp;&quot;
    }
    return (text)
  &#93;&#93;&gt;&lt;/function&gt;[/code:2rt1rf6b]
